    <section id="id1170503607337">
      <title>SPELLING</title>
      <para id="id1170506246715">
        <emphasis effect="bold">1.Spelling can be fun!</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para id="id1170501158202">Game 1: Word chains</para>
      <list id="id1170502028481" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>You can play this game in groups.</item>
        <item>One person begins by writing down a word. The next person must begin the next word with the last letter of the previous word, e.g.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170507052746">Chewagoneverainbowestearacevilabel</para>
      <list id="id1170498788747" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>Can you circle your classroom with a word chain?</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170495881329">Game 2: Growing words</para>
      <para id="id1170502541909">Begin with a one letter word, such as i, a or o. Make the word grow, by adding one letter at a time. Each time you must make a new word, e.g.</para>
      <table id="id1170498764885" summary="">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
          <colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>a</entry>
              <entry>o</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>an</entry>
              <entry>do</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>ant</entry>
              <entry>nod</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>pant</entry>
              <entry>node</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>paint</entry>
              <entry>nodes</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>paints</entry>
              <entry/>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
      <para id="id1170506983531"> Challenge your friends to see how long a list they can make.</para>
      <para id="id1170494534683">Game 3: Word-loop</para>
      <list id="id1170502250830" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>Decipher this word-loop. Read clockwise.</item>
        <item>All letters are to be used. Do not use words more than once.</item>
        <item>Sometimes small words may be found within bigger ones.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170496850480">Game 4: Time Trials</para>
      <list id="id1170506257164" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>The challenge is: How many 1 / 2 / 3 / 4 syllable words, beginning with …, can you write down in 60 seconds:</item>
        <item>No dictionaries may be used. Break up into smaller groups to check each other’s words.</item>
        <item>Keep score, giving values to the words according to syllables / length.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170496909671">Game 5: Scrambled Eggs</para>
      <para id="id1170498066404">Just as all things are connected in this world, letters can be connected in so many different ways. Below are a bunch of eggs with a letter on each one. See how many words you can scramble up; but no jumping over the eggs!</para>
      <figure id="id1170500490475">
        <media id="id1170500490475_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/Picture 1-f6b5.png" id="id1170500490475__onlineimage" height="414" width="572"/>
        </media>
      </figure>
